14/12/2005
BRCKO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH, Croatia and Serbia sealed a trilateral agreement Tuesday (13 December) on co-operation in the reconstruction and development of sailing and transportation along the Sava River. 
The document was signed in Brcko. 
Officials estimate that the project would require financing of around 15m euros.
In other news, Croatian President Stipe Mesic and his Serbia-Montenegrin counterpart Svetozar Marovic jointly called for the preservation of a visa-free regime between their countries. 
Marovic made a daylong visit to Zagreb on Tuesday. 
(RTRS, PBS BiH, HINA, Beta - 13/12/05)
